    <!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutral Harmony -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application uses a tab-based navigation structure to separate "Lexical" and "Grammar" topics, which is intuitive for the user. The core content is displayed as a grid of interactive cards. This approach allows for easy scanning of topics. Clicking a card opens a modal with details, preventing clutter on the main screen. A key feature is the progress tracking system (status buttons on cards and a summary donut chart), which gamifies the learning process and provides clear visual feedback. This structure was chosen to transform a static list into a dynamic and engaging tool for managing the learning journey. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: List of lexical and grammar topics. -> Goal: Organize, inform, and track progress. -> Viz/Presentation Method: Interactive cards for topics (HTML/Tailwind), a donut chart for overall progress (Chart.js), and a modal for detailed information (HTML/JS). -> Interaction: Users can filter topics by category, view details by clicking cards, and update the status of each topic. The chart updates dynamically with each status change. -> Justification: This combination of elements provides a clear, organized, and motivating user experience. It avoids static data presentation in favor of an interactive dashboard. -> Library/Method: Chart.js for data visualization, Tailwind CSS for styling, Vanilla JS for logic. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 320px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 320px;
        }
        .nav-button-active {
            background-color: #3b82f6;
            color: white;
        }
        .nav-button-inactive {
            background-color: #e5e7eb;
            color: #374151;
        }
        .status-btn {
            transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
        }
        .status-btn:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }
    </style>
